The paper deals with the problem of learning multiple concepts simultaneously, which is a core problem in machine learning (cs.LG). The authors also consider the problem in the context of differential privacy, which is a popular area of research in computer security (cs.CR). The paper involves analyzing the sample complexity of learning multiple concepts, which is related to the theory of computational complexity (cs.DS). The authors propose multi-learner algorithms, which involve designing efficient algorithms for learning multiple concepts, a topic that falls under artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper also involves analyzing the information-theoretic lower bounds on the sample complexity, which is related to information theory (cs.IT).
